The paper deals with congestion control in distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of probabilities and capacity constraints suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The mention of a protocol and memory usage suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of probabilities and convergence properties suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of memory usage suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
